==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*alda-'', from Indo-European ''*altos'', a suffixed form of ''*al-'' ‘grow, nourish’.  Cognate with Old Frisian ''ald'' (Frisian [[âld]]), Old Saxon ''ald'' (Dutch [[oud]]), Old High German [[alt]] (German [[alt]]).  Latin [[altus]] and Greek [[άναλτος]] are from the same IE root.

